data.text: @ambattii I think so? Not 100% sure of the terminology, but basically I have fairly visible eyelids, yeah.
@chelseakenna do you have hooded eyes? Ican't tell with your glasses but hooded eyes are better using thinner eyeliner anyway so I think that's good =x=
@ambattii I blame my nordic/celtic ancestors. My DNA was not meant to exist in a place with no rain and so much sun I think. XD

@ambattii Aw thank you! I have SUPER round eyes so heavy eyeliner actually makes my eyes look too crazy big. I spend a lot of time contouring my eyelids to elongate my eyes a bit so they're not so...buggy.
@chelseakenna I'm originally from New Mexico and the air there is so freaking dry I think Cali is soooo humid in comparison weep

@ambattii Yeah I think my skin just HATES the california air, even though I drink a ton of water. It sucks up all the moisture. XD I've always had problems though. My elbows and lips used to crack when I was younger before I discovered lotion & chapstick.
@chelseakenna OH BUT SEE THATS SO NATURAL LOOKING I LOVE IT I am too addicted/reliant on my thick eyeliner I can never go without it LOL
@ambattii Oh man that's so pretty! Your makeup game is way more pro than mine. This is a "good" makeup day for me XD https://t.co/fHwzHNVw4N
@chelseakenna drink like OBSCENE amounts of liquid every day so LOL;;

@chelseakenna https://t.co/1ipJgf3EG8 sry to throw selfies @ you but this is the look I did recently using a matte red liquid lipstick and I did the ombre effect with black matte eyeshadow *Q*

I feel like an alien sometimes bcuz I have never had issues with chapped/dry lips? but I--

@ambattii Yeah I love lipstick shading and highlighting! But also I just have chronically dry lips so I have to layer on moisturizing stuff no matter what (since long lasting lipsticks like liquid are too drying).
@chelseakenna i recently tried this ombre lipstick effect and it was so beautiful but takes a longtime...
@ambattii Although lately my everyday look is "Put hair in ponytail, make sure I am wearing a bra and real pants before leaving the house." Ahhh freelance/mom life.

@chelseakenna oh I understand this one =x= for my everyday lipstick look I usually just do a liquid or cream lipstick, if it's a dark or crazy color tho I have to spend extra time making sure its a clean application cuz dark colors are fucking bitches (and guess who loves vampy lip colors :/)
@ambattii Haha yeah I've definitely gotten faster with time. Hopefully someday I will be super speedy! I just haven't had as much practice. ;)
@chelseakenna oh hmm I see oxo Ya My every day look takes less time thanf ull glam look but my longest full glam makeup is like 30 mins ish... tho I've been wearing makeup since 6th grade so cry

@ambattii My lipstick sometimes takes a while too because I like to layer different lipsticks a lot (like a matte base and then a sheer shimmer, or lend colors) so I have to factor in drying time between coats.
@ambattii I do a bit more of an in-depth routine for cons/pro appearances (like a little blush/highlighter and stuff). But I think I'm just slow in general. I only started wearing makeup in my 20s.

@ambattii Depends on how my skin is that day. XD If I don't have much in the way of breakouts, then it's just a light tinted moisturizer, concealer as-needed, eyeshadow, eyeliner, mascara, and lipstick.
@chelseakenna omg no way oxo how much product are you using and is there smth in particular that slows you down oxo?
@ambattii I am insanely jealous of that speed. It takes me 15-30 min usually. Longer if we also count straightening my hair.
